HEADWORD: maiden blue-eyed mary
<hw>maiden blue-eyed mary</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small widely
branching Western wildflower (<spn>Collinsia parviflora</spn>) with tiny
blue-and-white flowers; found from British Columbia to Ontaria and south
to California and Colorado.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

